From: PureCloak Authors <purecloak-dev@purecloak.org>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 22:00:00 +0800
Subject: Expand GPU model database for fingerprinting diversity (#17)

Adds known NVIDIA and AMD GPU device IDs to the software rendering
list database. These entries serve as a registry of real GPU models
that PureCloak can reference when spoofing GPU identity for
fingerprinting diversity.

When PureCloak noise is enabled, all software_rendering_list entries
are bypassed by patch #32, so these entries never cause actual
blocklisting. They merely expand the internal database of known GPUs.

The following GPUs are added:
- NVIDIA GeForce GTX 1060/1070/1080 (Pascal)
- NVIDIA GeForce RTX 2060/2070/2080 Ti (Turing)
- NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3060/3070/3080 (Ampere)
- AMD Radeon RX 580 (Polaris)
- AMD Radeon RX 5700 XT (RDNA 1)
- AMD Radeon RX 6800 XT (RDNA 2)

